=== About ===
* Name: Fabrice Coutadeur
* Born in 1971, in France. Living in Spain, with my wife and my two children.
* Fluent French and Spanish speaker, I also speak English and a bit of German.
* Learned Computer Science at a French High School.
* Working as Product Manager in a European software company.
=== Contact details ===
*** Launchpad: https://launchpad.net/~fabricesp
*** Mail: coutadeurf@gmail.com
*** IRC: fabrice_sp on irc.freenode.net (#ubuntu-motu)
*** GPG public key: C0B161C9
=== Interest ===
Since I am 12 years old, I've been playing with computers: all began with a French MO6, for which I spent 6 month in programming in Basic a text game. Since then, I always have been playing/programming/working with a computer. My preferred language is C/C++ , but I also know Cobol.

I also try to communicate my passion for computers and for Ubuntu to my family and friends, having switched totally to Ubuntu since Hardy.

My main area of interest is video editing and encoding/transcoding (I've been Moderator of kvcd.net forum).
Apart from computers, I also love plants, especially Carnivorous plants.

<nowiki>[[FabriceCoutadeur-UniverseContributorApplication|Universe Contributor Developper]]</nowiki> since 13/03/2009

==== Personal Package Archive ====
I'm actually using my ppa as a test for new packages, so that users can download them and check if it works correctly, and also to backport some bugfixing release that don't justify a SRU.

I'm also using my ppa to test packaging of some new packages, before uploading to REVU.

You can find it <nowiki>[[https://launchpad.net/~fabricesp/+archive/ppa|there]]</nowiki>
